cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it deals with the task of generating natural language descriptions of source code. It could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it discusses the use of code summarization in software documentation. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of datasets for training models. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is also a possibility as the paper deals with the retrieval of relevant information from source code. Finally, Programming Languages (cs.PL) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the differences between natural language and source code.
